==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Declaratory
<hw>De*clar"a*to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧claratoire</ets>.]</ety> <def>Making declaration,
explanation, or exhibition; making clear or manifest; affirmative;
expressive; <as>as, a clause <ex>declaratory</ex> of the will of the
legislature</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Declaratory act</b></col> <fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd>an act or
statute which sets forth more clearly, and declares what is, the
existing law.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Declare</ent>⟦br⟧
